# SellAuth visual editor (theme 156746)

Builder: https://dash.sellauth.com/builder/visual/156746

This theme is built to be **resold**. Anything a buyer sees on the storefront must be changeable in the SellAuth visual editor without editing code.

## Before shipping any component

1. **schema.json** — add or extend the component entry with every user-facing field (titles, subtitles, lists, links, toggles).
2. **settings.json** — seed `properties` with the current copy so the builder preview matches production.
3. **Template** — wire copy through `properties.* | renderString | default('…')`, never hardcode marketing text in `.njk`.
4. **Builder markers** — root element: `class="component"` + `data-component-id="{{ componentId }}"`.
5. **Validate** — after each new section, open the visual builder and confirm fields appear and update the preview.

## Mock UI (hero peek, feature panels, how-it-works demos)

- Decorative mocks are **optional**, not core content. Expose a toggle per section: `show_mock_ui` (or `show_hero_mock`).
- When off: do not render mock markup; JS must no-op if the section/root is missing.
- Document in schema `help` that mock chrome uses demo labels — buyers who disable mocks get copy + layout only.
- Prefer real product/checkout flows over fake UI when the platform provides data.

## Snippets

Snippets rendered from components receive `properties` explicitly:

```nunjucks
{% render_snippet "home-steps.njk", properties=properties, componentId=componentId %}
```

Inside snippets, treat `properties` as the single source of truth for editable copy.

## Skill maintenance

After **major UI/UX work** on this theme (new sections, layout patterns, motion, mock patterns, token changes):

- Update `.cursor/skills/beautiful-mysellauth-themes/SKILL.md` and the relevant `references/*.md` so future builds inherit the improvement.
- Capture new builder field patterns, anti-patterns, and quality checks — do not leave knowledge only in theme files.

## Checklist (every PR / session touching theme UI)

- [ ] No new hardcoded headline, CTA, or FAQ aside text
- [ ] schema.json + settings.json updated together
- [ ] Mock sections have an off toggle
- [ ] Builder preview tested (Ctrl+F5 after watch push)
